  <bioghist id="aspace_dd8c975270fb6a8dcd858b9e5912eefb">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Lawyer, judge, mayor of Ithaca, New York.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_59b7a5a80a5573319ef41425fc34f0e9">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Primarily legal papers pertaining to various cases over which Judge Horton presided while Justice of the New York State Supreme Court, 6th Judicial District or as a private attorney. Includes typed charges to the jury, printed appeal books, and a few letters; also, correspondence and papers (1917-1919) relating to the Ithaca Calendar Clock Company, of which Horton was a trustee, mainly in connection with its going into receivership and with its dissolution.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_c90482bae118568273f7b5c43075b978">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Randolph Horton papers, #1799. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
